==Events== *[[1513]] &ndash; Spanish explorer [[Juan Ponce de León]] first sights land in what is now the [[United States]] state of [[Florida]]. *[[1755]] &ndash; [[Commodore (Royal Navy)|Commodore]] [[William James (naval commander)|William James]] captures the [[Maratha]] fortress of [[Suvarnadurg]] on west coast of India. *[[1792]] &ndash; The [[Coinage Act of 1792|Coinage Act]] is passed establishing the [[United States Mint]]. *[[1800]] &ndash; [[Ludwig van Beethoven]] leads the premiere of his [[Symphony No. 1 (Beethoven)|First Symphony]] in [[Vienna]]. * 1800 &ndash; The [[Treaty of Constantinople (1800)|Treaty of Constantinople]] establishes the [[Septinsular Republic]], the first autonomous Greek state since the [[Fall of the Byzantine Empire]]. *[[1801]] &ndash; [[French Revolutionary Wars]]: The British [[Battle of Copenhagen (1801)|capture]] the Danish fleet. *[[1851]] &ndash; [[Mongkut|Rama IV]] is crowned [[Monarchy of Thailand|King]] of [[Thailand]]. *[[1863]] &ndash; [[American Civil War]]: The largest in a series of [[Southern bread riots]] occurs in [[Richmond, Virginia]]. *[[1865]] &ndash; American Civil War: Defeat at the [[Third Battle of Petersburg]] forces the [[Army of Northern Virginia]] and the Confederate government to abandon [[Richmond, Virginia]]. *[[1885]] &ndash; Canadian [[Cree]] warriors [[Frog Lake Massacre|attack]] the village of [[Frog Lake, Alberta|Frog Lake]], killing nine. *[[1900]] &ndash; The [[United States Congress]] passes the [[Foraker Act]], giving [[Puerto Rico]] limited [[self-rule]]. *[[1902]] &ndash; [[Dmitry Sipyagin]], [[Ministry of Internal Affairs (Russia)|Minister of Interior]] of the [[Russian Empire]], is assassinated in the [[Marie Palace]], [[Saint Petersburg]]. * 1902 &ndash; "Electric Theatre", the first full-time [[movie theater]] in the United States, opens in [[Los Angeles]]. *[[1911]] &ndash; The [[Australian Bureau of Statistics]] conducts the country's first [[Census in Australia|national census]]. *[[1912]] &ndash; The ill-fated {{RMS|Titanic}} begins [[sea trial]]s. *[[1917]] &ndash; [[World War I]]: United States President [[Woodrow Wilson]] asks the [[United States Congress|U.S. Congress]] for a [[declaration of war]] on [[German Empire|Germany]]. *[[1921]] &ndash; The [[Autonomous Government of Khorasan]], a military government encompassing the modern state of [[Iran]], is established. *[[1930]] &ndash; After the mysterious death of Empress [[Zewditu]], [[Haile Selassie]] is proclaimed emperor of [[Ethiopia]]. *[[1956]] &ndash; ''[[As the World Turns]]'' and ''[[The Edge of Night]]'' premiere on [[CBS]]. The two soaps become the first daytime dramas to debut in the 30-minute format. *[[1972]] &ndash; Actor [[Charlie Chaplin]] returns to the United States for the first time since being labeled a [[Communism|communist]] during the [[Second Red Scare|Red Scare]] in the early 1950s. *[[1973]] &ndash; Launch of the [[LexisNexis]] computerized legal research service. *[[1975]] &ndash; [[Vietnam War]]: Thousands of civilian [[refugee]]s flee from [[Quảng Ngãi Province]] in front of advancing [[North Vietnam]]ese troops. *[[1976]] &ndash; Prince [[Norodom Sihanouk]] resigns as leader of [[Cambodia]] and is placed under [[house arrest]].<ref>{{cite book|author=Osborne, Milton E|title=Sihanouk Prince of Light, Prince of Darkness|year=1994|publisher=University of Hawaii Press|location=Honolulu, Hawaii, United States of America|isbn=978-0-8248-1639-1|page=223}}</ref> *[[1979]] &ndash; A Soviet bio-warfare laboratory at Sverdlovsk [[Sverdlovsk anthrax leak|accidentally releases airborne anthrax spores]], killing 66 plus an unknown amount of livestock. *[[1980]] &ndash; United States President [[Jimmy Carter]] signs the [[Crude Oil]] [[Windfall Profits Tax]] Act. *[[1982]] &ndash; [[Falklands War]]: [[1982 invasion of the Falkland Islands|Argentina invades the Falkland Islands]]. *[[1986]] &ndash; [[Alabama]] governor [[George Wallace]], a former [[segregationist]], best known for the "[[Stand in the Schoolhouse Door]]", announces that he will not seek a fifth four-year term and will retire from public life upon the end of his term in January 1987. *[[1989]] &ndash; [[Soviet Union|Soviet]] leader [[Mikhail Gorbachev]] arrives in [[Havana]], [[Cuba]], to meet with [[Fidel Castro]] in an attempt to mend strained relations. *[[1989]] &ndash; [[ASUS]] corporation was founded. *[[1991]] &ndash; [[Rita Johnston]] becomes the first female [[Premier (Canada)|Premier]] of a [[province (Canada)|Canadian province]] when she succeeds [[William Vander Zalm]] (who had resigned) as [[Premier of British Columbia]]. *[[1992]] &ndash; In [[New York (state)|New York]], [[American Mafia|Mafia]] boss [[John Gotti]] is convicted of murder and [[racketeering]] and is later [[Life imprisonment|sentenced to life]] in prison. * 1992 &ndash; Forty-two civilians [[Bijeljina massacre|were massacred]] in the town of [[Bijeljina]] in [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]]. *[[2002]] &ndash; [[Israel]]i forces [[Siege of the Church of the Nativity in Bethlehem|surround the Church of the Nativity]] in [[Bethlehem]] into which armed [[Palestinians]] had retreated. *[[2004]] &ndash; [[Islamism|Islamist]] [[terrorism|terrorists]] involved in the [[11 March 2004 Madrid attacks]] attempt to bomb the Spanish high-speed train [[AVE]] near [[Madrid]]; the attack is thwarted. *[[2006]] &ndash; Over 60 [[tornado]]es [[April 2, 2006 tornado outbreak|break out]] in the United States; [[Tennessee]] is hardest hit with 29 people killed. *[[2012]] &ndash; A [[Oikos University shooting|mass shooting at Oikos University in California]] leaves seven people dead and three injured. *[[2014]] &ndash; A [[2014 Fort Hood shooting|spree shooting]] occurs at the [[Fort Hood]] army base in Texas, with four dead, including the gunman, and 16 others injured. *[[2015]] &ndash; Gunmen [[Garissa University College attack|attack]] [[Garissa University College]] in [[Kenya]], killing at least 148 people and wounding 79 others. * 2015 &ndash; Four men [[Hatton Garden safe deposit burglary|steal]] items worth up to £200 million from an underground [[safe deposit]] facility in London's [[Hatton Garden]] area in what has been called the "largest burglary in English legal history."<ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-london-34899627 | title=Hatton Garden raid 'largest in English history' | work=BBC News | date=23 November 2015 | accessdate=23 November 2015}}</ref>
